<section class="hero">
    <h1><em>Borrowing</em> Against Your Stack</h1>
    <div class="hero-subtitle">Bitcoin as collateral instead of selling it &mdash; with HODL as the legitimate baseline and the structural risks made fully visible.</div>
    <p class="subtitle">The reflex to dismiss borrowing-against-bitcoin as anti-ethos misses the most important question: <em>compared to what?</em> When the alternative is selling part of your stack to fund a genuine life-event need, the borrow-and-retain path deserves careful evaluation against its actual risks. This page is built to make that evaluation possible &mdash; and to make it possible to walk away on reflection, knowing exactly what you're walking away from.</p>
</section>

